  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Legal Aid for Indigents in Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ghana&apos;s justice system does not guarantee free legal services for the poor and less-privileged persons who are unable to hire counsel to represent them. A State-funded legal aid scheme is woefully under-funded and ill-equipped to make any impact and there is no effective private alternative. Consequently, accused persons who cannot afford the services of counsel mostly end up in jail. HelpLaw Ghana is providing free legal assistance for these unfortunate citizens who are being denied justice.</narrative>
  </description>
